## What docs page needs to be fixed?
https://github.com/reduxjs/redux/blob/master/docs/recipes/WritingTests.md

- **Section**: Connected components
- **Page**: https://redux.js.org/recipes/writing-tests

## What is the problem?
There are a few variables which are undefined in the examples (I was only interested in testing for connected components, so I didn't get around to reading the rest of the document).

For example:
```javascript
import { connect } from 'react-redux'

const App = props => {
  return <div>{props.user}</div>
}

export default connect(mapStateToProps)(App)
```

`mapStateToProps` is undefined here, and
```javascript
// test-utils.js
import React from 'react'
import { render as rtlRender } from '@testing-library/react'
import { createStore } from 'redux'
import { Provider } from 'react-redux'

function render(
  ui,
  {
    initialState,
    store = createStore(reducer, initialState),
    ...renderOptions
  } = {}
) {
  function Wrapper({ children }) {
    return <Provider store={store}>{children}</Provider>
  }
  return rtlRender(ui, { wrapper: Wrapper, ...renderOptions })
}

// re-export everything
export * from '@testing-library/react'
// override render method
export { render }
```
`reducer` is undefined here.

## What should be changed to fix the problem?
I'm not familiar with Redux, but it would be nice to have minimal working examples for `mapStateToProps` and `reducer`. I tried running this test out of `create-react-app` boilerplate and it errored out. If fixing this part of the docs is approachable by a beginner in a few days' time I can certainly try and fix it in my spare time.
